SENATE RESOLUTION 101
By Oliver
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate Chara Rand on her
selection as the 2024–2025 Metro Nashville
Public Schools Principal of the Year and Middle
School Principal of the Year.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that we should pause to specially recognize those outstanding
professionals who have devoted their careers to providing the highest-quality education for
Tennessee's students; and
WHEREAS, Chara Rand is one such estimable administrator, who has distinguished
herself as a professional of the greatest dedication, ability, and integrity; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Rand has been selected as the 2024–2025 Metro Nashville Public
Schools Principal of the Year and Middle School Principal of the Year, most befitting honors that
recognize the positive influence she has on so many young lives; and
WHEREAS, under Chara Rand's leadership as principal, Isaac Litton Middle School has
continued to thrive, emphasizing academic excellence, student well-being, and a strong sense
of community; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Rand is an extremely talented and compassionate administrator who
works assiduously to motivate her students, teachers, and staff to reach their full potential as
scholars, professionals, and citizens; and
WHEREAS, she serves as an inspiration to the faculty and staff of Isaac Litton Middle
School, and her friendship and counsel are highly valued by those who are fortunate to know
her; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Rand truly epitomizes the dedicated principal who is wholly committed
to the highest ideals of public service and quality education for all, and she should be specially
recognized; now, therefore,
